{"id":197074,"name":null,"username":"Battler","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png","created_at":"2004-10-14T10:30:31.000Z","cooked":"<p>- Gobbles: hacking the .EXE file is not a good idea for such big things. I tried to hack the LBA 2 .EXE file, in order, to display texts RTL (right-to-left), but I didnt succeed, since for RTL, I needed extra lines to be put into the code, which cant be done by hacking the .EXE file, as you cant change its size, otherwise, it wont work. Sorry. But it is possible. Just we have to modify the scenes, redirecting some points into isometric scenes, instead of 3-D ones (I think there is some code in the scenes, which decides, whether to load a 3-D environment, or an isometric one). So, we should think about this solution</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":23,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T17:06:33.563Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7611,"topic_slug":"an-all-isometric-lba2","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":1083,"username":"Gobbles","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/gobbles/{size}/218_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"\\- Gobbles: hacking the .EXE file is not a good idea for such big things. I tried to hack the LBA 2 .EXE file, in order, to display texts RTL (right-to-left), but I didn't succeed, since for RTL, I needed extra lines to be put into the code, which can't be done by hacking the .EXE file, as you can't change its size, otherwise, it won't work. Sorry. But... it is possible. Just we have to modify the scenes, redirecting some points into isometric scenes, instead of 3-D ones (I think there is some code in the scenes, which decides, whether to load a 3-D environment, or an isometric one). So, we should think about this solution...","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1016,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/an-all-isometric-lba2/7611/4","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}
{"id":197078,"name":null,"username":"xesf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png","created_at":"2004-10-14T10:34:36.000Z","cooked":"<p>Inst possible.</p>\n<p>Youll need to make the isometric island design, thing that we cant make it now and when could be possible will be an hard work. Other thing most hard is to modify the scenes.hqr. The 3D scenes will not match the 2D scenes and will need to be re-write.</p>\n<p>Well if making an No CD crack its a little difficult in some cases, changing the way the Engine works will be impossible</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":23,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T17:06:33.704Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7611,"topic_slug":"an-all-isometric-lba2","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":1083,"username":"Gobbles","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/gobbles/{size}/218_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"Ins't possible. \n\nYou'll need to make the isometric island design, thing that we can't make it now and when could be possible will be an hard work. Other thing most hard is to modify the scenes.hqr. The 3D scenes will not match the 2D scenes and will need to be re-write.\n\nWell if making an \"No CD crack\" its a little difficult in some cases, changing the way the Engine works will be impossible...","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"group_moderator":true,"user_id":463,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/an-all-isometric-lba2/7611/5","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}
{"id":197080,"name":null,"username":"Battler","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png","created_at":"2004-10-14T12:41:42.000Z","cooked":"<p>- alexfont: if we preserve the original 3D positions in the isometric scene, then, the SCENE.HQR files would be OK, and they would just need a simple correction, in order to load isometric environment, instead of the 3D one. Actually, there would be no need to hack the .EXE files, nor to completely rewrite the scene files. So, its worth considering.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":23,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T17:06:33.774Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7611,"topic_slug":"an-all-isometric-lba2","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":1083,"username":"Gobbles","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/gobbles/{size}/218_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"\\- alexfont: if we preserve the original 3D positions in the isometric scene, then, the SCENE.HQR files would be OK, and they would just need a simple correction, in order to load isometric environment, instead of the 3D one. Actually, there would be no need to hack the .EXE files, nor to completely rewrite the scene files. So, it's worth considering.","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1016,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"w