{"id":197164,"name":null,"username":"xesf","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png","created_at":"2004-10-15T10:50:10.000Z","cooked":"<p>I continue thinking this is an impossible/extremellyhard job to do.</p>\n<p>Anyway I think scene files have a paramenter to distinguish the outside and inside scene in the zones. In this way will be necessary change all the zones that connect to the outside scenes. Will be necessary too, add the Grids and Layouts in the LBA_Bkg file, and this could be another problem. The LBA2 saved game in the holomap var game use bitfields to distinguish the outside and inside scenes, probably other var game made the same.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":23,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T17:06:36.767Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7611,"topic_slug":"an-all-isometric-lba2","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":1083,"username":"Gobbles","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/gobbles/{size}/218_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"I continue thinking this is an impossible/extremellyhard job to do.\n\nAnyway I think scene files have a paramenter to distinguish the outside and inside scene in the zones. In this way will be necessary change all the zones that connect to the outside scenes. Will be necessary too, add the Grids and Layouts in the LBA_Bkg file, and this could be another problem. The LBA2 saved game in the holomap var game use bitfields to distinguish the outside and inside scenes, probably other var game made the same.","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"group_moderator":true,"user_id":463,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/an-all-isometric-lba2/7611/11","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}
{"id":197169,"name":null,"username":"Battler","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png","created_at":"2004-10-15T11:10:23.000Z","cooked":"<p>- alexfont:</p>\n<p>I meant this: in all LBA 2 scene files, at the beginning, there is (I think) a bit, that determines, whether the scene is isometric (LBA_BKG.HQR) or 3-D (*.ILE). If its 3-D, then it also specifies the index of the island, which data it has to load (or multiple, if there are various option, like for Citadel Island and Celebration Island), and then, it specifies, which part of the island it has to load (again, with the index). Of course, with 3-D scenes, all other parts (of the same island) are also loaded, to display the whole 3-D island. We just have to know, how to hack the bits.</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":23,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T17:06:36.957Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7611,"topic_slug":"an-all-isometric-lba2","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":1083,"username":"Gobbles","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/gobbles/{size}/218_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"\\- alexfont:\n \n I meant this: in all LBA 2 scene files, at the beginning, there is (I think) a bit, that determines, whether the scene is isometric (LBA_BKG.HQR) or 3-D (*.ILE). If it's 3-D, then it also specifies the index of the island, which data it has to load (or multiple, if there are various option, like for Citadel Island and Celebration Island), and then, it specifies, which part of the island it has to load (again, with the index). Of course, with 3-D scenes, all other parts (of the same island) are also loaded, to display the whole 3-D island. We just have to know, how to hack the bits.","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1016,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/an-all-isometric-lba2/7611/12","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}
